stershire, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Hende","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of Family Names in Britain and Ireland © University of the West of England 2016","meanings":["English, Scottish: nickname from Middle English  <i>hend(e)</i> ‘courtly, refined; handsome; valiant’ (Old English  <i>(ge)hende</i>)."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Alice","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Originally a variant of   Adelaide  , representing an Old French spelling of a reduced form of Germanic <i>Adalheidis</i>. <i>Alice</i> and <i>Adelaide</i> were already regarded as distinct names in English during the medieval period. <i>Alice</i> enjoyed a surge of popularity in the 19th century and periods of favour ever since. It was the name of the central character of  Lewis Carroll's  Alice's Adventures in Wonderland (  1865 ) and Through the Looking Glass (  1872 ), who was based on his child friend  Alice Liddell , daughter of the Dean of Christ Church, Oxford."],"variants":[{"name":"Alys","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Alice ."]},{"name":"Alis","meanings":["equivalent of <b>Alice</b> ."]}]},{"name":"Millicent","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From an Old French name, <i>Melisende</i>, of Germanic (Frankish) origin, from <i>amal</i> ‘labour’ + <i>swinth</i> ‘strength’. This was the name of a daughter of Charlemagne. It was adopted by the Normans and introduced by them to Britain."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705195,"age":22,"year":"1382","julianDay":2225826,"title":"Wycliffe's Bible","description":"John Wycliffe, English theologian and professor at the University of Oxford, completed a translation of the Bible from the Latin Vulgate into Middle English. This translation is known as Wycliffe's Bible and was completed around 1382.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wycliffe%27s_Bible","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Wycliffe's Bible","jurisdictionLevel":0}],"lifeSummary":"When Alice Millicent Hende was born in 1360, in England, her father, Lord John Hende, was 21 and her mother, Katherine, was 20. She married Robert Laynham in 1382, in Rutland, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. She died in 1446, in Todenham, Gloucestershire, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 86, and was buried in Todenham, Gloucestershire, England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"1360–1446":"1360–1446","1360–1418":"1360–1418","1400–1447":"1400–1447","1340–1418":"1340–1418","1340–1407":"1340–1407","1340":"1340","1360":"1360","Abt 1400":"umbes 1400","1382":"1382","Bef 1407":"enne 1407","1380":"1382","1 August 1418":"1. august 1418","1447":"1447","1446":"1446","1400":"1400","1 Aug 1418":"1. august 1418","1407":"1407","1418":"1418","Essex County, England":"Essex, England","Warwick, England, United Kingdom":"Warwickshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Rutland, England":"Rutland, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Toddenham, Gloucestershire, England":"Todenham, Gloucestershire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1360–1446":"1360–1446","1360–1418":"1360–1418","1400–1447":"1400–1447","1340–1418":"1340–1418","1340–1407":"1340–1407","1340":"1340","1360":"1360","Abt 1400":"noin 1400","1382":"1382","Bef 1407":"ennen vuotta 1407","1380":"1382","1 August 1418":"1. elokuuta 1418","1447":"1447","1446":"1446","1400":"1400","1 Aug 1418":"1. elokuuta 1418","1407":"1407","1418":"1418","Essex County, England":"Essex, England","Warwick, England, United Kingdom":"Warwickshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","England":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Rutland, England":"Rutland, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Toddenham, Gloucestershire, England":"Todenham, Gloucestershire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1360–1446":"1360–1446","1360–1418":"1360–1418","1400–1447":"1400–1447","1340–1418":"1340–1418","1340–14